    if age > 17:
        return True
    else:
        return False

Create a function to fix it and apply it.¶

In [171]:
def fix_century(x):
  year = x.year - 100 if x.year > 1989 else x.year
  return datetime.date(year, x.month, x.day)

data['Yr_Mo_Dy'] = data['Yr_Mo_Dy'].apply(fix_century)
